Source: The White House, Fact Sheet: President Donald J. Trump Safeguards Venezuelan Oil Revenue for the Good of the American and Venezuelan People. Date on page: January 9, 2026. URL: https://www.whitehouse.gov/fact-sheets/2026/01/fact-sheet-president-donald-j-trump-safeguards-venezuelan-oil-revenue-for-the-good-of-the-american-and-venezuelan-people/

Extracted relevant page text:
- President Trump signed an Executive Order declaring a national emergency to safeguard Venezuelan oil revenue held in U.S. Treasury accounts from attachment or judicial process, preserving the funds to advance U.S. foreign policy objectives.
- Foreign Government Deposit Funds are defined as Venezuelan oil revenues and diluent sales held in U.S. Treasury accounts.
- The order affirms the funds are sovereign property of Venezuela held in U.S. custody for governmental and diplomatic purposes.
- The White House says loss of control over these revenues would weaken efforts to bring peace, prosperity, and stability to Venezuela and the Western Hemisphere.
- The fact sheet states: President Trump authorized lethal force against narcoterrorists to stop the flow of deadly drugs into this country.
- It states: President Trump ordered a total and complete blockade of all sanctioned oil tankers going in and out of Venezuela.
- It states: President Trump offered multiple off ramps to Maduro and his illegitimate regime, but he was clear that the drug trafficking must stop.
- It states: Last week, U.S. armed forces conducted an extraordinary military operation in support of law enforcement to bring outlaw dictator Maduro to justice.
- It states that the President's actions reestablish deterrence in the Western hemisphere and that safeguarding these oil revenues promotes stability in Venezuela while advancing U.S. objectives.